By Iyiola Pedro Renowned human rights activist, Femi Falana (SAN) has hit hard on the private sector and churches as being nests of corruption, more  than government institutions. Falana made the remark at the 2018 edition of the Vanguard Economic Discourse, themed: “Economy in Recession: Pitfalls, Trajectories and Resetting” The event held at The Civic Centre, Victoria Island, Lagos. 